Text.SourceString: Oh yeah, yeah! I heard about you.//You’re that new farmer from San Franciskyo, right?//<portrait=normal>Ah, that’s right! <Italic>Pokyo</>.//I’m <NPCName>Theo</>.
Me? I’m from here. I fish for a living.
There are so many microplastics in the sea.//<portrait=annoyed>You’d be surprised how much trash I can gather in just one day out fishing.

One time, I was walking past the recycling center when inspiration struck.//<portrait=concerned>What could I do to help? My heart was set, and that was it.//<portrait=happy>I stopped and hung out there for two days, writing a song about recyclables.
It goes: Who were you~ Plastic bottle~ Where did you come frooooom~ A lump of trash~ Dooooo doo doo dooooo doodooooo~
There are so many microplastics in the sea.//<portrait=annoyed>You’d be surprised how much trash I can gather in just one day out fishing.

One time, I was walking past the recycling center when inspiration struck.//<portrait=concerned>What could I do to help? My heart was set, and that was it.//<portrait=happy>I stopped and hung out there for two days, writing a song about recyclables.
It goes: Who were you~ Plastic bottle~ Where did you come frooooom~ A lump of trash~ Dooooo doo doo dooooo doodooooo~

I might try my hand at gardening one of these days.//<portrait=happy>I bet it’s a great outlet for self-expression.//<portrait=normal>All I need is a little piece of land and some seeds from <NpcName>Sam</>.
Now isn’t the time…//<portrait=happy>I’m waiting for my calling to farm before I start.//<portrait=normal>Won’t be too long… I can feel it coming on soon.

I might try my hand at gardening one of these days.//<portrait=happy>I bet it’s a great outlet for self-expression.//<portrait=normal>All I need is a little piece of land and some seeds from <NpcName>Sam</>.
Now isn’t the time…//<portrait=happy>I’m waiting for my calling to farm before I start.//<portrait=normal>Won’t be too long… I can feel it coming on soon.
Oh, can you really tell?!//<portrait=happy>Yeah, my guitar and singing skills are both self-taught.
I refuse to pay for one of those shallow classes.//<portrait=angry>They don’t teach you how to really express yourself. They only teach you how to make pretty noises.
In this day and age, people can be so greedy.//We always want more and more and more.//<portrait=sad>It’s sad, really.
Let me tell you something I learned, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Happy people are happy ’cause happiness comes from within, not from the endless pursuit of wealth.
Maybe I’ll buy a new boat someday. But even then, it won’t be the new boat that makes me happy.//<portrait=happy>Fishing makes me happy.
We need to take time to know ourselves.//That’s the only way to find out what we really enjoy without pressure from other people.
Oh! I forgot!//<portrait=concerned>I’m meeting my friends at the community center today.//<portrait=sad>Oh, no, no. Hang on. That’s tomorrow!
I don’t have a favorite kind of music. I like any song that’s made with love.//When I’m listening, all I hear is the love the creator put in.
What about you? What’s your favorite music genre?
The beach and the sea are my favorite places.//The sea is so peaceful, isn’t it? It shelters millions of lives, yet it remains so humble.
I live with my sister and dad by the lake. It gets spooky at night.
Heh heh… Kidding. It doesn’t, I’m just messing with you.//<portrait=normal>But there are wild animals around here, so they might be responsible for any weird noises the townies hear.
I used to be nervous about the whole not-having-an-office-job thing or not going the traditional route like my sister did.//Not anymore, though.
I am who I am, and there’s nothing wrong with that.//<portrait=happy>People may call me boring, but I know myself better.//<portrait=normal>I’m not boring or unmotivated… I’m laid-back.
I think we owe it to ourselves to be happy.//And the key to happiness is being content with what you’ve got.
I have no idea why I’m telling you all this. It’s like I had no choice but to say those things.//<portrait=angry>Weird.
Anyone can catch legendary fish at sea with enough skill.//<portrait=normal>They’re hard to find, but not impossible.
<NpcName>Sunny</> is a big name around here.//He used to hunt legendary monster fish!
I’m not actively hunting for legendary fish.//I don’t see the appeal.
What are you gonna do this weekend?
I sing live on weekends.//<portrait=happy>I don’t make much, but I can always use the tips.
I really appreciate <NpcName>Betty</> for taking it into her own hands to feed the wild birds.
Any big plans for the day?
Dad is a fisher, but he doesn’t fish so much anymore.//<portrait=concerned>Too old for the night wind, he says.
He helps <NpcName>Sunny</> run the Beach Shack full-time now.
Wealth isn’t everything, <PlayerName>$player</>. Don’t waste your life chasing it.
It’s great to see you out and about!//<portrait=normal>Living on a big farm can be quite isolating.
[<NpcName>Theo</> seems to be deep in thought.]
Dad is a fisher, but he doesn’t fish so much anymore.//<portrait=concerned>Too old for the night wind, he says.
He helps <NpcName>Sunny</> run the Beach Shack full-time now.
My sister is right, it isn’t about us being independent…//Living at home is a tradition in our family. It’s been like that for generations.
My uncles and aunts all lived at home until they were married.
*[<NpcName>Theo</> seems to be deep in thought.]
Dad is a fisher, but he doesn’t fish so much anymore.//<portrait=concerned>Too old for the night wind, he says.
He helps <NpcName>Sunny</> run the Beach Shack full-time now.
Wealth isn’t everything, <PlayerName>$player</>. Don’t waste your life chasing it.
It’s great to see you out and about!//<portrait=normal>Living on a big farm can be quite isolating.
For a while, I tried making a living as a truck driver, but it can get pretty lonely on the road.
I guess being away from family for too long just isn’t for me.//<portrait=normal>The pay was good, though.
The thing about playing the guitar is that you have to feel it in your gut first.//<portrait=normal>Then it will flow out through the melody.
Feeeeel it, <PlayerName>$player</>.
For a while, I tried making a living as a truck driver, but it can get pretty lonely on the road.
I guess being away from family for too long just isn’t for me.//<portrait=normal>The pay was good, though.

I met all sorts of folks on the road.//<portrait=happy>This one time, I met this guy with a really thick mustache, and he had a talking hat.//<portrait=normal>Nothing magic about it, though. It was a robot that he built.
There’s a song in there. I can feel it!
I’m not in the mood for pasta tonight, but I suppose it’s all we’ve got.//<portrait=sad><NPCName>Lily’s</> too busy to run to the store, and I keep forgetting.
I should pick up some greens for the fridge. Hmm…
Should I go to Sam’s, or should I just run to the woodland real quick?
Oh, since I have you here… I have something to ask.//Did you by any chance give my sister a diamond?//<portrait=annoyed>It wasn’t you, was it?
Never mind, then…//My sister was upset the other day because she said that somebody was trying to buy her affection.//She was given a diamond, and she kind of lost it. Poor thing.
The thing about playing the guitar is that you have to feel it in your gut first.//<portrait=normal>Then it will flow out through the melody.
Feeeeel it, <PlayerName>$player</>.
<NpcName>Lily</> gets so upset when someone gives her pearls or gold bars.//<portrait=normal>She’s a sensitive soul.//Now, if you want to get on her good side, give her some kind of food instead.
Oh, like what? Hmm, let’s see.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Lily</> loves pancakes, omurice… Hmm, what else?
Laaaaa… laaaaa~ Coral reefs… Coral, coral reefs~ Deep in blue sea… You’re old and pretty~ Laaaaa~//<portrait=blushing>What do you think? Not bad, huh?
…You’re leaving me hanging here, bud…
Oh, <PlayerName>$player</>, want to hear my new song? I wrote it yesterday.
Flowers~ You beautiful flowers~ As beauuuuutiful as the eyes of my love~
This is usually the season when a lot of fish eggs hatch.//I had to release a lot of fish back to the ocean the other day because they were too small.
Doesn’t all this new life make you feel inspired, <PlayerName>$player</>? The birth of new creatures also means the birth of new ideas.
I’m looking forward to the Cherry Blossom Festival.//I’ve got a couple of new songs I want to play.
You hear that, <PlayerName>$player</>? I only wish I could sing as great as the birds. So carefree and beautiful.

The island is so alive with music, <PlayerName>$player</>.//The crashing of the waves, the chirping of the birds, and even the rustling of the new leaves come together to make this beautiful Spring music.
It’s so much nicer to go out there and fish now.//I don’t have to stand in the freezing cold anymore.
I caught a tuna the other day, so I guess we’re entering Summer now.
The Summer breeze feels different on my face… A little saltier than Spring, if you want to know.
I see seals, turtles, all kinds of wild animals swimming to shore in Summer.//<portrait=normal>I talk to them sometimes too, for fun.
The heat’s getting to me, <PlayerName>$player</>. Should I go for a swim?//<portrait=normal>I might if you will too…
Nice cold milk sounds good…but I probably shouldn’t.//It upsets my stomach, and my day’s just begun.
I wouldn’t sail too far if I were you.//Not in this heat. You might run into a storm at sea… Not saying you would.
<NPCName>Sunny</> is the defending champion in the swimming contest. //<portrait=surprised>I don’t understand how he can swim so fast at his age!
Ha! Never really realized how glowing you look in the Summer heat.//It suits you.
I don’t know why all the songs I’m writing are super sad lately. Here’s what I wrote yesterday.
“The lifeless leaves have left my life.” What a downer.
I’m still singing and writing songs, but it’s harder for me to do in Fall.
You know how I know it’s Fall? I caught plenty of cod yesterday!
I woke up today, and I didn’t feel too good. Then I looked at the calendar.//This is the week when we lost Mom…
Summer was cool. I caught plenty of tuna. The Beach Shack was pretty happy…//Today is a different story.
I’m not a big fan of Fall.//I don’t hate it… It’s all right.
Didn’t catch a lot of fish today, but I still managed to catch a yellowfin tuna. Must be Winter!
Are you looking forward to the New Year’s Eve Festival, <PlayerName>$player</>? There’s usually a lot of good food and fun games!//I’ll be singing too… Got some new tunes here in the brain!
It can be dangerous to go out on the ocean in Winter, but if you’re trained and you’re careful, everything should turn out fine.
Is it too cold to eat ice cream? Maybe, but I certainly wouldn’t say no if somebody offered me one!
Some fish don’t stick around in Winter. They go… They swim away to warmer waters.
Like what? Hmm…let’s see. Rainbow fish aren’t Winter fish. They’re Fall.//Cobia too, I think.
A lot of things happened this past year. Two people and a corporate office moved in.
I’m just glad that people are seeing the potential in this island.
I hope this new year gives you a chance for a fresh start, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Whether that means taking another run at your goals or maybe setting some new ones.
Making peace with myself was the hardest thing I’ve ever done.//Now I take every day as it comes, with an extra dose of gratitude.
It’s a bit of a tradition for me to bring fresh fish to the Cherry Blossom Festival.//<portrait=happy>My dad would always bring his smoked salmon.
And I’ll open the festival with a song of my own.//<portrait=happy>Drives the crowds wild.
*yawns* I’m still tired from singing all day yesterday.
Oh, I’m happy singing here, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I don’t need some fancy label to tell me how to live.
Today I wanna focus on my soul and just feed my brain some thoughts.
My throat feels scratchy…//<portrait=sad>Must be from eating too many banana fritters last night.
Either that, or I’m developing a pollen allergy. Hmm…
One of these days, I’ll go fishing at your farm.//I’m interested in surveying the area to see what kinds of fish swim there.
Not today, though. Maybe when the water is a bit cooler.
Why do I feel like there’s a new bug in town every Summer?
I could really go for some ice cream right now.
I’m taking the day off for the Beach Cleanup Festival so I can participate.
I’ve been bringing in more trash than usual when I fish. Have you noticed that too?
It’s a pity, really. But hopefully, it’ll get better and better every day.
The change in the season never really bothers me. I still fish… I still sing.
I don’t pay much attention to the calendar. Too constricting.//I usually notice the seasons changing by the type of fish I catch.
Let’s see what I can come up with for a Fall song.
[<NpcName>Theo</> seems to be deep in thought.]
Happy harvest season, Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>!
Oh, hang on… I have Fall melodies coming into my mind. Dum~ Dum~
Singing in the rain? Now that is an idea.
I don’t know how I feel about that. It just seems… Cold.
Money was never really a thing for me. My dad was a fisher his whole life, and Mom was a diver.//We had a pretty great life overall.
Growing up, I knew some people who had a lot more than we did, but they weren’t half as happy.
I almost slipped on the ice this morning. You be careful out there, <PlayerName>$player</>!
One of my favorite things about Winter is all the festive decorations. They make the town feel so alive.
Making peace with myself was the hardest thing I’ve ever done.//Now I take every day as it comes, with an extra dose of gratitude.
I don’t travel a lot. Like, travel for leisure, you know. But I’ve gone places for work, and I’ve seen things.
I guess being away from my family for too long just isn’t for me.
I’m a bit chilly. Might need to put on a coat.
This place has that damp aura about it, and the rain makes it worse.
My boat isn’t the most reliable in the rain, so I better stick to fishing on sunny days.
[<NpcName>Theo</> is in a rush.]
[<NpcName>Theo</> is in a rush.]
I’m a bit chilly. Might need to put on a coat.
This place has that damp aura about it, and the rain makes it worse.
My boat isn’t the most reliable in the rain, so I better stick to fishing on sunny days.
It gets dark so early lately.
[<NpcName>Theo</> is in a rush.]
[<NpcName>Theo</> is in a rush.]
One of my favorite things about Winter is all the festive decorations. They make the town feel so alive.
It gets dark so early lately.
It gets dark so fast in Winter.
What if I write a song about Winter and cheerful bells?//<portrait=happy>Bells jingling and people singing along and laughing.
Hmm… Doesn’t ring a bell.//<portrait=annoyed>You sure you got the melody right?
It gets dark so early lately.
I’m in the mood for something crunchy.
[<NpcName>Theo</> is singing – better not bother him.]
Any song requests, <PlayerName>$player</>?
This gig isn’t really banking the big bucks for me. But it isn’t always about the money, ya know?//<portrait=happy>It’s about doing something that you love.
<PlayerName>$player</>, are you here for me?//<portrait=surprised>Nah! Just messing with you!//<portrait=happy>Grab a seat, I’m about to sing. You won’t want to miss this.
I had a really filling, super meal that <NpcName>Frank</> made yesterday.//<portrait=normal>I don’t know if there’s any left, but you should try it if you can.
Oy, <NpcName>Frank</>! Make one of those super meals for <PlayerName>$player</>, will ya?
Ah yes, here I am indeed. Where else would I be? I’m a fisher, after all.
I went to the lookout the other day and saw your farm. You’ve done a great job with it, <PlayerName>$player</>!
I sing to soothe my soul. Hopefully, it has the same effect on anyone who hears it.
I already delivered some of my catch to the Beach Shack.//I’m hoping to catch a bit more before the day ends.
Meh, fishing during the day is enough for me.//<portrait=normal>I don’t need to fish at night too.
You’re welcome to join the meeting here, <PlayerName>$player</>…//<portrait=normal>No pressure.
I come here whenever I feel like things are a bit overwhelming.//<portrait=normal>But I also come sometimes just to share something about my day.//Sometimes a little company is all we need.
It’s hard to break a habit. But I’m taking it one day at a time.//With the right support system, I believe that any of us can do it.
Nothing in this world is easy, <PlayerName>$player</>.//But taking it step by step helps a lot!
I’m lucky I got out when I could.//<portrait=sad>I didn’t know what would happen to my family or me if I…
Never mind.
I always used to feel like I was waiting for something. Without knowing what it was.//<portrait=sad>It felt like torture.
Now I’m not waiting anymore.//<portrait=happy>I’m living…
[<NpcName>Theo</> seems to be concentrating.]
Sure are a lot of books in the library…
Do you think anyone’s read all these books?
I hope you didn’t come here looking for a song, because I’m not here to sing.
It’s just raining so hard outside, so…//Um… What was your question?
I really like this positive glow that you bring, <PlayerName>$player</>. Always puts a smile on my face.
Hey, anyone ever told you you’re just so easy to talk to? I appreciate that.
A good listener, you are.
It’s not that I don’t want to accept my mother’s death. It’s just…
I don’t know.
How can you fully accept someone being gone forever?
Now that my mother’s memory is all I’ve got, it has to be enough, doesn’t it?//<portrait=sad>But what if it’s not enough? Where else do I look?
Dad once said that all any parent ever wants is for their children to be happy. I think he was right. I think that’s what my mother would’ve wanted for <NpcName>Lily</> and me.
Make no mistake, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m going to pursue happiness. I won’t disappoint my mother.
You must be mad fit, working day in and day out on that big farm.//Teach me your secret sometime, will ya?
I’m not <NpcName>Theo</> the fisher today. Today I am <NpcName>Theo</>, the singer!
Sing a ballad with me, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I used to sing to <NpcName>Lily</> all the time when we were kids. She loved it.
Ask her! She’ll tell you the same thing. If you can get her to talk to you, that is.//<portrait=sad>She can seem…distant sometimes.
If you ever need a friend, come and find me.//You’re always there for me… I owe you. A lot.
If you need anything done…favor or…<Italic>anything</>… I’m your guy.
Ugh… I gave in to temptation and had some milk this morning. I hate myself.//<portrait=angry>Milk doesn’t agree with me. It hurts me.//It’s brought me nothing but pain.
My stomach hurts.
If I had a keg, I would make strawberry juice all year long and nothing else.//I might just start farming strawberries and do it anyway.
Hmm… Hang on. Do you need a keg or a jar to make juice?//<portrait=concerned>Hmm… In any case, it’s one of those. You know what I’m talking about.
Come hang out with me at the beach sometime, will ya?//<portrait=normal>It gets pretty lonely up there… I could use the company.
Or you could come over to my house if you prefer… It’s more private.
I left my window open last night, and a cat sneaked into my bedroom this morning.//I freaked out and jumped out of bed so fast. My head went all fuzzy, and I couldn’t see for a good few seconds.
That was really weird! I can still feel my ears popping.
<NpcName>Lily</> and Dad are everything to me.//<portrait=sad>Ever since Mom passed away, I can’t bear the thought of being away from them.
I hate to talk about it, but I guess talking about it is the first step in acknowledging my feelings.//<portrait=normal>Here goes nothing.
My heart broke when Dad came home to tell us that Mom had an accident while diving. It still hurts.//I’m afraid this feeling will never go away.

It’s hard for me to let Mom go. She was still so young. It just doesn’t feel right, <PlayerName>$player</>.//She had a whole life ahead of her, but she was taken so suddenly. We were just little kids.
…I never got to say goodbye.

I can think of a way to pay you back…for all your help and the good times I’ve had talking with you.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I could come over to your farm and take care of things for you for a change.
Water some crops or something… What do you think?
You live near <NpcName>Kenny’s</>, right? If you see him, will you tell him to come see me?//I’ve been looking for him all Summer.
I found one of his flutes behind my house, I think.//I told him about it when I ran into him at the store, but he still hasn’t picked it up yet.
Spending too much time in crowds isn’t good for my soul.//It drains my creativity. That’s why I only perform on weekends.
I like spending time with you.//<portrait=blushing>It energizes me… I wish I could do it more often.
Spring is extra pretty with you around.
Use extra blankets tonight, will you?//I don’t want you to get cold.
Winter isn’t so bad now that you’re around.
I learned to make fish tacos the other day, and they turned out pretty good.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I can make some for you sometime.
Your eyes are flowers~ And your smile is my world~
That’s a no, then? I was just trying out a new song, but I wasn’t feeling it either, to be honest.
Yeah? You like? I worked so hard on that.//<portrait=happy>I can feel it. This one is going to be a hit.
I’m glad you like it. I was on my boat yesterday, thinking about you, and the song just came to me.//<portrait=happy>You should come over sometime, and I’ll play you the rest.
Aww, <PlayerName>$player</>. Stop looking at me like that.//You’re making me blush!
My neck feels a bit stiff. Ugh… I guess I slept on it funny last night, but I didn’t think it would last this long.
It’s because I slept on my belly.//<portrait=annoyed>My neck is usually back to normal within a couple of hours. It’s never taken this long.
Don’t worry too much if you wake up with a sore neck. It’ll get better in time.//The thing is… Neck is neck. It gets sore once in a while.
You look extra cute today!//Spring suits you.
You look extra cute today!//Fall looks good on you.
Sleeping is great… It’s even better when it’s snowing out.//Sleep soothes the mind. It’s an important part of the day.
